definitions.definition: Used to briefly refer to a noun phrase understood by context

subdefinitions.definition: One o'clock , either a.m. or p.m.
One run scored by hitting the ball and running between the wickets ; a single .

examples: Did you hear the one about the agnostic dyslexic insomniac ?

subdefinitions.definition: An alcoholic drink , especially a pint or can of beer.
examples: I had a quick one after work
There’s nothing better than drinking a cold one when the weather’s boiling outside
Just a quick one before work

definitions.definition: A person or thing ( having some specified characteristic or attribute ).
examples: Well, well, well, it seems the silent one does have a voice, after all.
That's the one to watch if you want to win.

subdefinitions.definition: A person with a tendency to do something.
examples: He's not one for pulling his punches.

subdefinitions.label_groups: archaic , ironic or endearing ; following an adjective

definitions.definition: A particularly special or compatible person or thing.
examples: I knew as soon I met him that John was the one for me and we were married within a month.
That car's the one — I'll buy it.

definitions.definition: The identity element with respect to multiplication in a ring .
Deliberate misspelling of ! , used to amplify an exclamation, parodying unskilled typists who forget to press the shift key while typing exclamation points, thus typing "1" .
examples: A: SUM1 Hl3p ME im alwyz L0ziN!1!?1!
B: y d0nt u just g0 away l0zer!!1!! one !! one !!eleven!!1! Why don't you just go away loser!
y d0nt u just g0 away l0zer!!1!! one !! one !!eleven!!1!
